title: Zucchini Pasta And Grilled Fish
summary: Zucchini Pastan And Grilled Fish is a pescatarian main course. For $5.53 per serving, this recipe covers 52% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. One serving contains 799 calories, 63g of protein, and 17g of fat. This recipe serves 4. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around 45 minutes. A mixture of spaghetti, garlic, pepper, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so delicious. To use up the salt you could follow this main course with the Apple Turnovers Recipe as a dessert. 5 people were impressed by this recipe. It can be enjoyed any time, but it is especially good for The Fourth Of July. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 95%. This score is awesome. Try Grilled Asparagus and Zucchini Pasta, Grilled Sea Bass over Zucchini Pasta with Roasted Tomatoes, and Whole-Wheat Pasta Salad with Grilled Zucchini and Olives for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: No one wine will suit every pasta dish. Pasta in a tomato-based sauce will usually work well with a medium-bodied red, such as a montepulciano or chianti. Pasta with seafood or pesto will fare better with a light-bodied white, such as a pinot grigio. Cheese-heavy pasta can pair well with red or white - you might try a sangiovese wine for hard cheeses and a chardonnay for soft cheeses. We may be able to make a better recommendation if you ask again with a specific pasta dish.
